				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Lute of the Flowing Waters<a name="27139"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 12 04 5:40 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>grats on your lute. You're xp'ing will never be the same.
<br />

<br />
With the insta cast wind of marr, you can add a song to your twist now. The way I do it with my ornate greaves (with 1 sec selo's on them) is to click and hold the item slot which you can then drop into one of your hotkey slots. Your lute is clickable from inventory so just drop it in a top level inventory slot and hotkey that slot the same way. The normal use of 11 22 33 44 to twist songs is still there, you just need to click any other song to stop it. (if it doesn't stop itself like the greaves don't). so if you drop the lute inventory slot into your 6th hotkey slot for example, your twist would look like 1 22 33 44 46 11 22 33 44 46 (the 46 set being 4 to stop song and 6 to play since clicking the item won't stop song, so you just use the previous song to stop instead of the next and back to the beginning to stop song 6 using song 1 to stop it and start 1 again.)
<br />

<br />
bah that almost looks like too complicated of an explaination but I'm sure you realize what I mean. Just picture it if you used the song you just played to stop itself instead of the next song in the twist to stop the last, twists would look like 1 12 23 34 41, but you only need to do it for that one clicky that can't stop songs.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
