				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Lute of the Flowing Waters<a name="27480"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 13 04 6:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Make a hotkey that only has /stopsong on it.
<br />
Make a hotkey that has the lute on it.
<br />

<br />
Map both these hotkeys to the same button in options.
<br />
Now you can press that button twice to stopsong, and cast the clicky. If a song is running, the button will function as /stopsong, if no song is running it will do the lute clicky.
<br />

<br />
Ie I have my lute on PGdown, and my other normal twist keys are del, ins, home, with macros looking like /stopsong; /cast X... so my twist with lute is:
<br />
Ins, wait 3 secs
<br />
Home, wait 3 secs
<br />
PGDown, PGdown
<br />
Del, wait 3 secs
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
